<!-- WHAT IS SHOWER SILICONE -->
<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-primary tracking-tighter mb-4">What Is Shower Silicone?</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary max-w-3xl mb-10">Many people confuse silicone with grout. They're different materials that do different jobs. Here's a quick guide so you know exactly what we're talking about.</p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-error mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">location_on</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Where You'll Find It</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Silicone is the flexible rubber-like sealant in your shower corners, along the floor-wall junction, around tap fittings, and where any two surfaces meet at an angle. It's usually a thin bead that fills the gap where tiles can't butt directly together.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-error mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">water_drop</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Why It Goes Mouldy</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Shower corners and floor junctions are where water collects and ventilation is poorest. The silicone bead sits in constant moisture. Over time, mould spores settle on the surface and gradually grow into the body of the silicone itself, turning it black.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-error mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">cleaning_services</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Why Cleaning Doesn't Work</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Bleach and mould sprays only kill mould on the surface. But silicone is porous at a microscopic level &mdash; once mould has grown into the material, no amount of scrubbing will reach it. You clean it, it looks better for a week, then the black comes back.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-error mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">grid_view</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">How It Differs from Grout</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Grout is the hard, rigid material between your tiles in a grid pattern. Silicone is the flexible sealant at junctions and corners. They serve different purposes &mdash; grout fills the lines between tiles, silicone seals where movement occurs. This page is about the silicone.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- WHY BAD SILICONE IS A PROBLEM -->
<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-surface-container-low">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-primary tracking-tighter mb-4">Why Bad Silicone Is a Problem</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary max-w-3xl mb-10">Mouldy silicone isn't just an eyesore. It's a sign that the seal has failed &mdash; and that means trouble.</p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 max-w-4xl">
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border-l-4 border-error reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-2xl text-error mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">water_damage</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Water Leaks</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Silicone exists to keep water out of the gaps between surfaces. When it deteriorates or pulls away from the tile, water can seep behind your walls and under floors. Over time this damages the waterproofing membrane and structural timbers &mdash; repairs that cost thousands.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border-l-4 border-error reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-2xl text-error mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">bug_report</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Health Concerns</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Black mould in your shower releases spores into the air you breathe while showering. Prolonged exposure to mould spores can irritate airways and aggravate respiratory conditions like asthma. A bathroom you use daily should be mould-free.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border-l-4 border-error reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-2xl text-error mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">trending_down</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Appearance &amp; Value</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Black mouldy silicone is one of the first things people notice in a bathroom. It makes the whole room look unclean regardless of how often you scrub. If you're selling or renting, it's a red flag that puts off buyers and tenants instantly.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- HOW WE REPLACE IT -->
<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-primary tracking-tighter mb-4">How We Replace It</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary max-w-3xl mb-10">Our five-step process ensures the old mouldy silicone is completely removed and replaced with a clean, lasting seal.</p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">1</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Strip Old Silicone Completely</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">Using specialty scraping tools and blades, we remove every trace of the old mouldy silicone from all corners, floor-wall junctions, and around fixtures. Nothing is left behind &mdash; new silicone won't bond properly over old residue.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">2</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Clean &amp; Treat Surfaces</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">Once the old silicone is out, we clean all exposed surfaces and apply an anti-mould treatment solution. This kills any mould spores that may have reached the tile edges or substrate, giving the new silicone a clean foundation.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">3</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Mask Edges with Tape</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">We apply masking tape along both sides of every junction to ensure perfectly straight, clean lines. This is the difference between a professional finish and a DIY job &mdash; crisp edges that look neat and stay sealed.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">4</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Apply Premium Silicone</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">We apply premium wet-area silicone in a continuous bead along every junction. The silicone we use is specifically rated for bathroom environments with built-in anti-fungal properties for long-term mould resistance.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">5</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Tool &amp; Finish</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">Each bead is tooled smooth with a profiling tool for a consistent, concave finish that sheds water properly. The tape is removed while the silicone is still wet, leaving perfectly clean lines and a watertight seal throughout your shower.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

